.TH SDL_LoadFile_IO 3 "SDL 3.1.3" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_LoadFile_IO \- Load all the data from an SDL data stream\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_iostream\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "void * SDL_LoadFile_IO(SDL_IOStream *src, size_t *datasize, bool closeio);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The data is allocated with a zero byte at the end (null terminated) for
convenience\[char46] This extra byte is not included in the value reported via
.BR datasize
\[char46]

The data should be freed with 
.BR SDL_free
()\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I src
the 
.BR SDL_IOStream
 to read all available data from\[char46]
.TP
.I datasize
a pointer filled in with the number of bytes read, may be NULL\[char46]
.TP
.I closeio
if true, calls 
.BR SDL_CloseIO
() on
.BR src
before returning, even in the case of an error\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the data or NULL on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

